+## PR-214 Reply Draft
+
+### T-214-01
+
+Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py` and `src/policy/approval_router.py`. The fallback payload now keeps `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`, and the router normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before building either preview shape.
+
+### T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. This thread reports the same reopened fallback preview regression, so the fix above covers it without a second code path.
+
+### T-214-03
+
+Not applied. This thread points at an outdated hunk and suggests reviving legacy preview behavior on the current branch. I intentionally did not restore that path.
+
+### T-214-04
+
+Added a regression test in `tests/test_preview.py` covering `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"`. The assertion now verifies fallback status plus normalized `approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review=True`.
+
+### T-214-05
+
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example matches the corrected payload and explicitly includes `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
