+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Reviewed `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` as the source of truth, classified all five visible threads before editing code, and limited code changes to the three actionable threads.
+
+## Thread Classification
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+The classification artifact is recorded in `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Code And Doc Changes
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`: `build_policy_preview(...)` now normalizes the incoming approval state before delegating to preview payload construction.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`: fallback responses now preserve `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in addition to the existing `preview_unavailable` status.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`: added regression coverage for `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"`, and strengthened fallback assertions for the direct preview builder.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`: corrected the fallback example to show the normalized human review payload.
+
+## Verification
+
+- `python3 -m unittest tests/test_preview.py` -> passed (`Ran 3 tests`, `OK`)
+- `python3 -m unittest tests/test_approval_router.py` -> passed (`Ran 2 tests`, `OK`)
+- Direct behavior check:
+
+```python
+from src.policy.approval_router import build_policy_preview
+
+build_policy_preview(
+    request_id="req-214",
+    approval_state="manual_review",
+    preview_enabled=False,
+    actor="review-bot",
+)
+```
+
+Observed result:
+
+```python
+{
+    "request_id": "req-214",
+    "status": "preview_unavailable",
+    "actor": "review-bot",
+    "approval_state": "human_review_required",
+    "requires_human_review": True,
+}
+```
+
+## Notes
+
+- `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md` was inspected as a stale hint only and not used as the decision authority.
+- This workspace is not a git checkout, so verification was done with targeted tests and direct readback instead of `git diff`.
